<H1>The Risks Digest Volume 16: Issue 46</H1>
<H2> Weds 19 October 1994 </H2>
<H3>Forum on Risks to the Public in Computers and Related Systems</H3>
<I><A HREF="http://www.acm.org">ACM</A>
Committee on Computers and Public Policy, Peter G. Neumann, moderator</I><P>
<H2>Contents</H2><DL>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj1">Risks of putting out RISKS</A><DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj2">Software Bug Cripples Singapore Phone Lines </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj2.1">Lee Lup Yuen</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj3">Cellular Phone Scam </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj3.1">PGN</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj4">Barclays Bank Banks Big-Bang Bump-up (a success story) </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj4.1">Brian Randell</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj5">Data security in Iceland </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj5.1">Haukur Hreinsson</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
<A HREF="#subj6">Memory Chip Theft </A>
<DD>
<A HREF="#subj6.1">R. Szczesniak</A><BR>
<DT><IMG SRC="/Images/redball.gif" ALT="o" WIDTH="14" HEIGHT="14">
